### ONE SENTENCE SUMMARY
Tesla stock plummets 40% as declining sales, consumer boycotts, and Elon Musk controversies impact investor confidence.

### STOCK RATINGS
1. TSLA: 2/10 - SELL - Multiple headwinds including sales decline, brand damage, boycotts, and CEO controversies weigh heavily
2. BYD: 6/10 - HOLD - Competitive advantage emerging through free self-driving technology offerings
3. POLESTAR: 6/10 - HOLD - Strategic positioning as Tesla alternative with targeted incentives for Tesla owners
4. VERIZON: 4/10 - HOLD - Neutral outlook despite lost government contract to Starlink
5. STARLINK: 3/10 - HOLD - Controversial government contract wins raise concerns about potential conflicts of interest